                </p>
               </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>Dîme <supplied reason="subaudible">consacrée à</supplied> Apollon.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p>Tithe <supplied reason="subaudible">dedicated to</supplied> Apollo.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p>Decima <supplied reason="subaudible">dedicata ad</supplied> Apollo.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>With the dative case of the god's name the word <foreign xml:lang="grc">δεκάτα</foreign> is usually at the accusative, see 
                    commentary at <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr106950</ref>.</p>
                <p/>
            </div></body>
